==English==
=== Etymology ===
From Swedish

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''ombudsman'''
# An [[appointed]] [[official]] whose duty is to [[investigate]] [[complaint]]s, generally on behalf of [[individual]]s such as [[consumer]]s or [[taxpayer]]s, against [[institutions]] such as [[companies]] and [[government department]]s. 

# Designated internal neutral in an organization whose duty is to assist employees with [[conflict resolution]] and other problems of employment and serve as independent consultant to recommend changes to policies or procedures to improve organization effectiveness and efficiency. Functions based on confidentiality, neutrality, independence and informality, reports to board of directors. 

